"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The numpy.sinc function computes the normalized sinc function, which is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). The expected values in the assertions are incorrect. For sinc(0), the result is indeed 1, but for sinc(1), the result is sin(pi)/(pi) which is approximately 0, not exactly 0.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n<assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n<assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0), \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\"\n}"